The paper deals with the problem of Face Anti-Spoofing (FAS) using machine learning techniques, specifically Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and Deep Forest. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the vulnerability of CNN-based methods to adversarial attacks, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of Deep Forest as an alternative to CNNs involves decision trees and ensemble learning, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also uses Local Binary Pattern (LBP) features, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
